{"parentUuid":"80d761f4-f605-4b3d-a62d-1ad88ffec3d8","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"2f1b9908-9d53-4078-951e-d73fd70bb335","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AWPfL4AgqaKFYPzUTXSKJ2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Data Description\n2\t\n3\t## Modalities\n4\t\n5\t### 1) 2p GCaMP (Source Sub-volume)\n6\t- Size: ~400 x 400 x 450 um (x x y x z)\n7\t- Resolution:\n8\t  - XY: ~0.78 um/pixel\n9\t  - Z: ~1 um/pixel (low axial resolution)\n10\t- Content:\n11\t  - GCaMP+ inhibitory neurons (~900 cells)  \n12\t  - 3D ROI segmentation data available\n13\t  - From pia surface. top ~50 um is blank buffer\n14\t- Nature:\n15\t  - Sub-volume embedded within HCR\n16\t\n17\t### 2) HCR Light-sheet (Target Volume)\n18\t- Size: ~1 x 1 x 0.5 mm (x x y x z)\n19\t- Resolution:\n20\t  - XY: ~0.24 um/pixel\n21\t  - Z: ~1 um/pixel\n22\t  - Zarr level 2 may have different xy resolution\n23\t- Content:\n24\t  - Ex vivo matched to the in vivo 2p volume, but larger\n25\t  - Rn28S (405): all cells (~100k)\n26\t  - GFP (488): GCaMP+ neurons\n27\t  - 3D ROI segmentation from Rn28S\n28\t  - GFP gene counts per ROI\n29\t  - Top part contains blank buffer, thickness unknown and varies across samples and within the sample (slanted).\n30\t\n31\t## Key Relationship\n32\t- 2p is localized inside HCR, roughly at the center, rotated 180 degress in xy plane (z axis fixed; this is not a flip)\n33\t- They both are from the surface of cortex (top part is pia surface)\n34\t- ROI segmentations have errors in both 2p and HCR data, so not 1-to-1 relation from 2p to HCR.\n35\t\n36\t## Transform\n37\t- anisotropic scaling\n38\t- nonrigid deformation\n39\t- smooth deformation\n40\t"}]},"uuid":"a11d1593-3f78-4c30-8897-09fb26757de2","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:49:46.104Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/capsule/code/docs/01 Data Description.md","content":"# Data Description\n\n## Modalities\n\n### 1) 2p GCaMP (Source Sub-volume)\n- Size: ~400 x 400 x 450 um (x x y x z)\n- Resolution:\n  - XY: ~0.78 um/pixel\n  - Z: ~1 um/pixel (low axial resolution)\n- Content:\n  - GCaMP+ inhibitory neurons (~900 cells)  \n  - 3D ROI segmentation data available\n  - From pia surface. top ~50 um is blank buffer\n- Nature:\n  - Sub-volume embedded within HCR\n\n### 2) HCR Light-sheet (Target Volume)\n- Size: ~1 x 1 x 0.5 mm (x x y x z)\n- Resolution:\n  - XY: ~0.24 um/pixel\n  - Z: ~1 um/pixel\n  - Zarr level 2 may have different xy resolution\n- Content:\n  - Ex vivo matched to the in vivo 2p volume, but larger\n  - Rn28S (405): all cells (~100k)\n  - GFP (488): GCaMP+ neurons\n  - 3D ROI segmentation from Rn28S\n  - GFP gene counts per ROI\n  - Top part contains blank buffer, thickness unknown and varies across samples and within the sample (slanted).\n\n## Key Relationship\n- 2p is localized inside HCR, roughly at the center, rotated 180 degress in xy plane (z axis fixed; this is not a flip)\n- They both are from the surface of cortex (top part is pia surface)\n- ROI segmentations have errors in both 2p and HCR data, so not 1-to-1 relation from 2p to HCR.\n\n## Transform\n- anisotropic scaling\n- nonrigid deformation\n- smooth deformation\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"80d761f4-f605-4b3d-a62d-1ad88ffec3d8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/root/capsule","sessionId":"32d07cf2-c20e-438b-a9af-caf182d4a09b","version":"2.1.101","gitBranch":"master","slug":"delightful-roaming-lamport"}
